verbose_text: Let-7 is known to target many oncogenes and " stemness " factors including c-Myc, Ras, HMGA2, NF-kappaB and Lin28 [XREF_BIBR] and studies in lung, breast and prostate cancer reveal that overexpression of let-7 inhibits cancer cell proliferation, in vitro clonal expansion and in vivo tumor regeneration by reducing c-Myc expression [XREF_BIBR].
